South African January Retail Sales Rose 10.6%, Led By Appliances, Clothing

-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 
2011-02-25T06:10:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-25/south-african-january-retail-sales-rose-10-6-led-by-appliances-clothing.html
South African retail sales rose 10.6
percent in January compared with a year ago, the Retailer
Liaison Committee, an industry group that includes Woolworths
Holdings Ltd., said in an e-mailed statement today.  Clothing and footwear rose 10.2 percent, furniture and
appliances by 22.7 percent, toys by 10.2 percent and other goods
by 10.1 percent, it said. Stationery sales declined 2.2 percent
and music and movie sales by 9.4 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  